      {
        "id": "C9YjFvzdDWT0VkuK",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Design Heuristics</strong></p><p>In this activity, you will use cards to help you transform your design solution ideas.  Look over your design idea sketches and notes. Then read the cards below. Choose one of the 8 cards to use. Then use that card to modify one of your design solution ideas. Sketch your new idea in the sketch boxes (or using pencil and paper). Write the title of the card you used in the sketch title box. </p><p>For example, I have an idea to make a watering chart for the school garden. I choose the card &quot;use less material.&quot; I have the idea that I could use less paper if I make the watering chart on a half sheet of paper or if I make the chart online using a google chart.  I decide to sketch the idea of an online watering chart. </p>"
          ]
        }
